{"usCongressBioId":"H000200","familyName":"Hare","givenName":"Butler","middleName":"Black","honorificPrefix":"Mr.","unaccentedFamilyName":"Hare","unaccentedGivenName":"Butler","unaccentedMiddleName":"Black","birthDate":"1875-11-25","birthCirca":false,"deathDate":"1967-12-30","deathCirca":false,"image":[{"contentUrl":"https://history.house.gov/Collection/Detail/25769818907","caption":"Collection of the U.S. House of Representatives <a href=\"https://history.house.gov/Collection/Detail/25769818907\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">About this object</a>"}],"profileText":"A Representative from South Carolina; born on a farm in Edgefield (now Saluda) County, near Leesville, S.C., November 25, 1875; attended the public schools; was graduated from Newberry (S.C.) College in 1899; taught in the public schools 1900-1903; secretary to Representative George W. Croft in 1904 and to his successor, Representative Theodore G. Croft, in 1905; professor of history and economics in Leesville (S.C.) College 1906-1908; special agent in the woman and child labor investigation conducted by the United States Bureau of Labor in 1908 and 1909; was graduated from George Washington University, Washington, D.C., in 1910, and from its law department in 1913; was admitted to the bar in 1913 and commenced practice in Saluda, S.C., in 1915; worked for the United States Department of Agriculture 1911-1924; engaged in agricultural pursuits; resumed the practice of law in Saluda, S.C., in 1924 and 1925; elected as a Democrat to the Sixty-ninth and to the three succeeding Congresses (March 4, 1925-March 3, 1933); chairman, Committee on Insular Affairs (Seventy-second Congress); was not a candidate for renomination in 1933; resumed his former pursuits; elected to the Seventy-sixth and to the three succeeding Congresses (January 3, 1939-January 3, 1947); unsuccessful candidate for renomination in 1946; resumed the practice of law and his agricultural pursuits; died in Saluda, S.C., December 30, 1967; interment in Travis Park Cemetery.","relationship":[{"relationshipType":"father","relatedTo":{"usCongressBioId":"H000202","familyName":"Hare","givenName":"James","middleName":"Butler","unaccentedFamilyName":"Hare","unaccentedGivenName":"James","unaccentedMiddleName":"Butler","birthDate":"1918","birthCirca":false,"deathDate":"1966","deathCirca":false}}],"jobPositions":[{"job":{"name":"Representative","jobType":"CongressMemberJob"},"startDate":"1945-01-03","startCirca":false,"congressAffiliation":{"congress":{"name":"The 79th United States Congress","congressNumber":79,"congressType":"USCongress","startDate":"1945-01-03","endDate":"1947-01-03"},"partyAffiliation":[{"party":{"name":"Democrat"}}],"caucusAffiliation":[{"party":{"name":"Democrat"}}],"represents":{"regionType":"DistrictRegion","regionCode":"SC"}}},{"job":{"name":"Representative","jobType":"CongressMemberJob"},"startDate":"1931-03-04","startCirca":false,"congressAffiliation":{"congress":{"name":"The 72nd United States Congress","congressNumber":72,"congressType":"USCongress","startDate":"1931-12-07","endDate":"1933-03-04"},"partyAffiliation":[{"party":{"name":"Democrat"}}],"caucusAffiliation":[{"party":{"name":"Democrat"}}],"represents":{"regionType":"DistrictRegion","regionCode":"SC"}}},{"job":{"name":"Representative","jobType":"CongressMemberJob"},"startDate":"1943-01-03","startCirca":false,"congressAffiliation":{"congress":{"name":"The 78th United States Congress","congressNumber":78,"congressType":"USCongress","startDate":"1943-01-03","endDate":"1945-01-03"},"partyAffiliation":[{"party":{"name":"Democrat"}}],"caucusAffiliation":[{"party":{"name":"Democrat"}}],"represents":{"regionType":"DistrictRegion","regionCode":"SC"}}},{"job":{"name":"Representative","jobType":"CongressMemberJob"},"startDate":"1925-03-04","startCirca":false,"congressAffiliation":{"congress":{"name":"The 69th United States Congress","congressNumber":69,"congressType":"USCongress","startDate":"1925-03-04","endDate":"1927-03-04"},"par